{"name": "safe-dencrypt", "metadata": {"name": "safe-dencrypt", "version": "0.2", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://kkgithub.com/ytsidle/safe-dencrypt", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A lib to decrypt or encrypt message convinet and safe!expert!", "upload_time": 1732983672}, "documentation": ["**\u8d85\u5b89\u5168\u52a0\u5bc6\u89e3\u5bc6\u5e93**\r\n\r\nsafecrypt\u662f\u4e00\u4e2a\u4e13\u4e1a\u52a0\u5bc6\u89e3\u5bc6\u5e93,\u53ea\u8981\u4e00\u4e2a\u5bc6\u7801,\u4e14\u62e5\u6709<u>\u5e9e\u5927</u>\u56e2\u961f~~(\u8db3\u8db3\u6709\u4e00\u4eba)~~\r\n\r\n\u5b89\u88c5\u65b9\u6cd5:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npip install safecrypt\r\n```\r\n\r\n\u4f7f\u7528\u65b9\u6cd5\r\n\r\n```python\r\nfuction nencrypt(str: string,str magic):\r\n    parm:string\r\n    explain:\u9700\u8981\u52a0\u5bc6\u7684\u6587\u672c,\u5fc5\u8981\r\n    parm:magic\r\n    explain:\u5bc6\u7801,\u975e\u5fc5\u8981\r\n    return:string\r\n    like 10010101010101.........\u6b64\u7c7b01\u7801,\u5f88\u957f\r\nfuction ndecrypt(str: string,str magic):\r\n    parm:string\r\n    explain:\u9700\u8981\u89e3\u5bc6\u7684\u6587\u672clike 10010101010101\u6b64\u7c7b01\u7801,\u5fc5\u8981\r\n    parm:magic\r\n    explain:\u5bc6\u7801,\u975e\u5fc5\u8981\r\n    return str:\u539f\u6587\u672c,\u4e00\u65e6\u6709error\u8fd4\u56deint:\u9519\u8bef\u7801-1\r\n   \r\n```\r\n\u4e14\u5bc6\u7801\u53ef\u4ee5\u662f\u4e2d\u6587\r\n\r\n\u66f4\u96be\u7834\u89e3\r\n\r\n\u5b89\u5168\u6027\u653e\u5fc3\u5427\r\n\r\n\r\nexample:\r\n\r\n```py\r\nimport safecrypt as s\r\na=s.nencrypt(\"123\")\r\nprint(a)\r\nb=s.ndecrypt(a)\r\nprint(b)\r\n```\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n00000000000000000000000000000000000000\r\n011000000011000000000000000000000000000\r\n000000000010001011000000000000000000000\r\n0000000000000000000000000001110011000000\r\n0000000000000000000000000000000011000001\r\n100000000000000000000